---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ContactSection from "../components/ContactSection.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";

const ticker = [
	"PHOTOGRAPHER",
	"DJ",
	"PROBLEM SOLVER",
	"FREELANCER",
	"MUSIC PRODUCER",
	"HUSBAND",
	"COFFEE GEEK",
	"HOUSE MUSIC ENJOYER",
	"GAME DEVELOPER",
];
---

<Layout title="Portfolio">
	<div>
		<!-- Hero -->
		<section class="min-h-[calc(100vh-3.5rem)] flex flex-col justify-between px-6 pt-16 pb-0 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
			<div style="animation: fade-up 0.6s ease-out both;">
				<h1
					class="text-foreground leading-none uppercase"
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(4rem, 14vw, 12rem); letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
				>
					SOFTWARE
					<br />
					<span style="color: var(--primary);">DEVELOPER</span>
				</h1>

				<p
					class="text-muted-foreground uppercase"
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-top: 0.25em;"
				>
					AND...
				</p>

				<!-- Scrolling ticker -->
				<div class="mt-6 border-t border-border overflow-hidden py-4">
					<div
						class="flex gap-12 whitespace-nowrap"
						style="animation: ticker 30s linear infinite; width: max-content;"
					>
						{
							ticker.map((item, i) => (
								<span
									class="text-muted-foreground"
									style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em;"
								>
									{item}
									<span style="color: var(--primary); margin-left: 3rem;">—</span>
								</span>
							))
						}
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start justify-between gap-8 mt-12">
					<p
						class="text-muted-foreground max-w-md"
						style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.6;"
					>
						Six years building backend systems in fintech — Java, Spring Boot, AWS. I recently started doing
						freelance projects on the side, and they've made clear what I want more of: work where I own
						more of the picture and stay close to the people using it.
					</p>
					<div
						class="text-muted-foreground"
						style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						BASED IN
						<br />
						<span class="text-foreground">CHICAGO, IL</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="pb-16"></div>
		</section>

		<!-- Projects CTA -->
		<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6" style="animation: fade-up 0.5s ease-out 0.2s both;">
			<Button href="/projects" class="gap-4 px-8 py-5">
				<span
					style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.3rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;"
				>
					VIEW ALL PROJECTS
				</span>
				<span style="font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem;">→</span>
			</Button>
		</section>

		<!-- About / Other Interests -->
		<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 mt-32">
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
				<!-- About -->
				<div>
					<h2
						class="text-foreground uppercase mb-8 border-b border-border pb-4"
						style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						ABOUT
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-4 text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.75;">
						<p>
							Based in Chicago since 2020, my professional background is backend engineering in fintech —
							Java, Spring Boot, lately a lot of AWS, REST APIs, data pipelines, integrations, the whole
							shebang. Over the last year I've had more room to actually shape things at work: from
							designing the backend of an analytics web app, to integrating my company's analytics data
							transformation functionality into a new ingestion pipeline, to sitting on cross-team
							meetings planning the architecture of an integrated client onboarding platform. That kind of
							ownership is relatively new for me, but I can confidently say it's been the most interesting
							professional work I've done yet.
						</p>
						<p>
							On the side I've been building for people I know — a site for a DJ collective's open-deck
							signups and events, a customizeable portfolio site for a DJ, my own wedding website. Nothing
							huge, but I got to watch real people use them. That's important to me, and I want more of
							that. I'm open to full-time roles, freelance, and contract work at any scale. What I care
							about is ownership and building something people actually use — products that help people
							get things done, creative tools, anything where I can see the impact.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Other interests -->
				<div>
					<h2
						class="text-foreground uppercase mb-8 border-b border-border pb-4"
						style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;"
					>
						OUTSIDE WORK
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="color: var(--primary); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;"
							>
								01
							</span>
							<div>
								<p
									class="text-foreground mb-1 uppercase"
									style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;"
								>
									MUSIC PRODUCTION
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
									I just recently started releasing music last year. House music — jazzy, bouncy,
									jackin', dub, I have a lot of influences. If that sounds like your vibe, check out
									my project Grid District.
									<Link href="/music" class="ml-1">MORE INFO</Link>
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="color: var(--primary); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;"
							>
								02
							</span>
							<div>
								<p
									class="text-foreground mb-1 uppercase"
									style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;"
								>
									DJING
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
									Something I picked up last year to get a bit closer to the local music scene. I've
									done a couple tiny shows at a local bar and coffee shop, but it's mostly a way for
									me to vibe with friends and more actively listen to my favorite tunes.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="color: var(--primary); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;"
							>
								03
							</span>
							<div>
								<p
									class="text-foreground mb-1 uppercase"
									style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;"
								>
									PHOTOGRAPHY
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
									I like to walk around and document my surroundings, be it architecture, people,
									spaces, or landscapes. Beynod serving as a relaxing vehicle for getting out the
									house and being more in-tune with my neighborhood, I've also covered a couple music
									shows and done portraits for friends.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="flex gap-6">
							<span
								class="shrink-0 mt-0.5"
								style="color: var(--primary); font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem;"
							>
								04
							</span>
							<div>
								<p
									class="text-foreground mb-1 uppercase"
									style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;"
								>
									BIKING
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted-foreground" style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">
									I got into biking a few years ago as a fun way to get some exercise in. I also enjoy
									tinkering and building up my 90's steel hybrid gravel conversion.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ContactSection />
	</div>
</Layout>
